# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

Modern vision-language models (VLMs) like LLaVA, PaliGemma, SmolVLM, Qwen2-VL, and Idefics3 accept both an image and a text prompt, then generate a text response. Transformers.js already has full model infrastructure for these (`AutoModelForImageTextToText`, `MODEL_FOR_IMAGE_TEXT_TO_TEXT_MAPPING_NAMES`, `imageTextToTextForward`), and the `AutoProcessor` variants that handle joint image+text preprocessing. What is missing is a pipeline class and SUPPORTED_TASKS registration to expose this to users via the `pipeline()` factory.

**Existing parallel:** `image-to-text` uses `AutoModelForVision2Seq` (encoder-decoder, image → caption). The new `image-text-to-text` targets decoder-only VLMs that require a text prompt too.

## Only One File Needs Editing: `src/pipelines.js`

Four precise changes, in order:

---

### Change 1 — Import `AutoModelForImageTextToText`

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js` lines 20–45, inside the `import { ... } from './models.js'` block.

**Add after `AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,` (line 43):**
```js
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,
```

`AutoModelForImageTextToText` is already exported from `src/models.js` line 8736. It only needs to be imported here.

---

### Change 2 — Add JSDoc Typedefs + Pipeline Class

**Location:** After line 2005 (closing `}` of `ImageToTextPipeline`), before line 2007 (start of `ImageClassificationPipeline` typedef).

Insert the following block:

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Generate text from an image and a text prompt.
 * @param {ImagePipelineInputs} images The input image(s).
 * @param {string|string[]} text The text prompt(s) to condition the generation.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments passed to the model's generate method.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput|ImageTextToTextOutput[]>} An object (or array of objects) containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */

/**
 * Image text to text pipeline using any `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline generates
 * text conditioned on an image and a text prompt, and can be used for tasks such as visual
 * question answering, image captioning with a prompt, and multimodal chat.
 *
 * **Example:** Answer a question about an image w/ `onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct`.
 * ```javascript
 * const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
 * const image = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const prompt = 'USER: <image>\nDescribe this image in one sentence.\nASSISTANT:';
 * const output = await pipe(image, prompt, { max_new_tokens: 50 });
 * // [{ generated_text: 'Two cats are resting together on a couch.' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(images, text, generate_kwargs = {}) {
        const isBatched = Array.isArray(images);
        const preparedImages = await prepareImages(images);

        const texts = Array.isArray(text) ? text : [text];

        // Modern VLM processors accept (images, text) together and return
        // {input_ids, attention_mask, pixel_values, ...} ready for generate().
        const inputs = await this.processor(preparedImages, texts, { padding: true });

        const outputTokenIds = /** @type {Tensor} */(await this.model.generate({
            ...inputs,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        }));

        // Decode full output (includes the prompt tokens for decoder-only VLMs).
        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(outputTokenIds, {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        });

        // Strip the prompt from each decoded string using the TextGenerationPipeline
        // pattern: decode the input_ids (skip special tokens) to measure prompt length,
        // then slice it off. Image placeholder tokens are special tokens and are skipped
        // by both decode calls, so lengths align correctly.
        const promptLengths = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(inputs.input_ids, {
            skip_special_tokens: true,
        }).map(x => x.length);

        const result = decoded.map((text, i) => ({
            generated_text: text.slice(promptLengths[i]).trim(),
        }));

        return isBatched ? result.map(x => [x]) : [result[0]];
    }
}
```

**Key design decisions:**

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| `_call(images, text, generate_kwargs)` | Modern VLMs require a prompt; making it a required param makes the API explicit |
| `prepareImages(images)` | Existing helper (line 91) normalises all image input types (URL, Blob, RawImage, etc.) |
| `processor(preparedImages, texts, {padding:true})` | Standard pattern for all VLM processors (LlavaProcessor, PaliGemmaProcessor, Qwen2VLProcessor, etc.) — one call returns merged image+text tensor dict |
| `model.generate({...inputs})` | Spreads processor output directly; `imageTextToTextForward` in models.js reads `pixel_values` + `input_ids` from the spread |
| Prompt-stripping via string length | Follows `TextGenerationPipeline` (lines 1053–1068) exactly; works at string level, not tensor level, avoiding Tensor.slice API ambiguity |
| Return shape for batched | `result.map(x => [x])` → `[[{generated_text}], [{generated_text}], ...]` matches `ImageToTextPipeline` convention |

---

### Change 3 — Register in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js` after the `"image-to-text"` entry (line 3255), before `"image-classification"` (line 3257).

Insert:
```js
    "image-text-to-text": {
        "tokenizer": AutoTokenizer,
        "pipeline": ImageTextToTextPipeline,
        "model": AutoModelForImageTextToText,
        "processor": AutoProcessor,
        "default": {
            "model": "onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct",
        },
        "type": "multimodal",
    },
```

`onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct` is the smallest production-quality VLM available as ONNX on the Hub, backed by `SmolVLMForConditionalGeneration` which is in `MODEL_FOR_IMAGE_TEXT_TO_TEXT_MAPPING_NAMES`.

---

### Change 4 — Update `pipeline()` Factory JSDoc

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js` ~line 3427, inside the `@param {T} task` listing.

Add after the `"image-to-text"` line:
```
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.
```

---

## Files Changed

| File | Nature of change |
|---|---|
| `src/pipelines.js` | Only file modified: import, new class, task registration, JSDoc update |

## Files NOT Changed (reused as-is)

| File | What's reused |
|---|---|
| `src/models.js` | `AutoModelForImageTextToText` (line 8736), `imageTextToTextForward` (line 819) |
| `src/models/auto/processing_auto.js` | `AutoProcessor` |
| `src/tokenizers.js` | `AutoTokenizer` |
| `src/pipelines.js` | `prepareImages()` (line 91), `Pipeline` base class (line 164), `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef (line 215) |

## Verification

**Manual smoke test:**
```javascript
import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';

const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
const output = await pipe(
  'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg',
  'USER: <image>\nWhat animals are in the image?\nASSISTANT:',
  { max_new_tokens: 50 }
);
console.log(output);
// Expected: [{ generated_text: 'Cats.' }] or similar
```

**Pipeline factory routing test:**
```javascript
import { pipeline, ImageTextToTextPipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';
const pipe = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'onnx-community/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
console.assert(pipe instanceof ImageTextToTextPipeline); // must pass
```

**Batch test:**
```javascript
const output = await pipe(
  ['img1.jpg', 'img2.jpg'],
  ['What is in image 1?', 'What is in image 2?'],
  { max_new_tokens: 20 }
);
// Expected: [[{generated_text: "..."}], [{generated_text: "..."}]]
```

**Existing pipeline regression:** Running existing tests must show no regressions — no existing pipeline code is modified.

